    ns1:numberOfCredits 3.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """This course is jointly offered with other Master Programmes.
The chronogram follows a theoretical planning of the subject and may undergo modifications during the course.
This Learning Guide is the general reference for this course.
The actual information about its implementation in the current semester (calendar, schedule, dates, deadlines, weights, notices, lists, etc.), will be published in the Moodle page of the course. Any conflict, deficiency, inconsistency or
discrepancy between the information in this guide and that published in Moodle must be resolved in favor of the latter.
The subject is related to:
SDG-4: Quality Education
SDG-5.5 Ensure women?s full and effective participation and equal opportunities for leadership at all levels of
decision-making in political, economic and public life
SDG-8: Decent Work and Economic Growth
The following innovative teaching methodology (https://innovacioneducativa.upm.es/guias-pdi) is implemented in the course in order to motivate and reinforce student learning:
Project-oriented learning: Throughout the course a project is proposed to be carried out in groups of a maximum of 4 people. The project includes several milestones, ranging from the proposal of the problem to be solved to the final implementation, through the stages of abstraction of data and tasks or the design and visual coding stage. Throughout the project, the teacher supervises the progress and the different milestones and provides continuous tutoring to resolve any doubts that may arise."""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Enero"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Septiembre"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Septiembre-Enero"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "30 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103001021/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description "This course will allow the student to gain the fundamentals for the visualization of all kinds of information. With an eminently practical approach, the technologies and fundamentals necessary to create successful information visualization tools will be presented."@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/pablo.toharia%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/a.latorre%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/jorge.acosta%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/pablo.toharia%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Data Visualization"@es .

